---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Creative Labs — Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Teaching kids to code and tutoring at Creative Labs Learning Center."
>
  <section class="hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Creative Labs Learning Center</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          Teaching, tutoring, and building the next generation of creators.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Story</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <p>
          My mom started Creative Labs Learning Center to give kids a space to learn and create. I've been part of it since the beginning — teaching coding basics, running summer camps, and tutoring students who need extra help.
        </p>
        <p>
          What I love about teaching is that it forces you to really understand something. If a 10-year-old asks "but why does the loop start at zero?", you better have a real answer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="what-i-do section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What I Do</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">💻</div>
          <h3>Coding Workshops</h3>
          <p>Teaching elementary students the basics of coding through fun, hands-on projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">📚</div>
          <h3>Math & Science Tutoring</h3>
          <p>One-on-one and small group tutoring to help students build confidence and master concepts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">☀️</div>
          <h3>Summer Camp Programs</h3>
          <p>Running week-long camps where kids build games, animations, and interactive projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Tech Mentoring</h3>
          <p>One-on-one mentoring for students who want to go deeper into programming and technology.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="learned section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What I've Learned From Teaching</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <ul class="learnings-list">
          <li>
            Explaining something simply is harder than understanding it yourself.
          </li>
          <li>
            Kids are fearless with code. They'll try things adults would never attempt.
          </li>
          <li>
            Teaching is the fastest way to find gaps in your own knowledge.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="connection section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="connection-content">
        <h2>The Connection</h2>
        <p>
          Teaching is why I build interactive visualizations — I want to see math concepts click for people the same way they click for me when I can see them visually.
        </p>
        <p class="connection-text">
          When a student finally understands why a loop works or how a function returns a value, that moment of clarity is what keeps me building tools that make learning visible.
        </p>
        <a href="/math-explorations" class="button">See My Math Explorations →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #27AE60 0%, #229954 100%);
    color: var(--white);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    opacity: 0.95;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
    }
  }

  .story,
  .learned {
    background-color: var(--white);
  }

  .what-i-do {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
  }

  .connection {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--white) 0%, var(--light-gray) 100%);
  }

  h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .content p {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .card {
    background-color: var(--white);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #27AE60;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  }

  .icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: #27AE60;
  }

  .card p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .learnings-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .learnings-list li {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    position: relative;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .learnings-list li {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
  }

  .learnings-list li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #27AE60;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .connection-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .connection-content h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .connection-content p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .connection-content p {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
  }

  .connection-text {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #27AE60;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .connection-content .button {
    display: inline-block;
  }
</style>
